channel.title: How thug-life feels about getting 100 days online{and his secret!}
channel.description:
<casey> Hello I am here with thug-life <casey> Thug-life how are you <Thug-life> fine <Thug-life> u <Thug-life> >?! <casey> Wonderful. <casey> Now how does it feel being hours from 100 days online? <Thug-life> No different than when i first joined the forum <casey> Do you consider yourself a nerd? <Thug-life> Depends what you mean by nerd <casey> As in you have no fucking life and spend your life on mopar <Thug-life> Well, i take my laptop to school & to college and click on mopar every now and then to check for new posts when i'm bored <Thug-life> so thats why i have an online time, i take my laptop most places <Thug-life> so i keep checking <Thug-life> but yah <Thug-life> i have no life <Thug-life> lulz <casey> Do you consider yourself a hero for 100 days online? <Thug-life> I consider myself a trend setter <casey> So you're saying others will follow, and be a person who has a life but no life like you? <Thug-life> Well if they follow my theory "If you enjoy staying in side more than going out, why do you have to do what you do not like to do? it is YOUR life do what you want with it". Then yeah <casey> Ok thank you for this epic chat, any closing words? <Thug-life> Allah is great <Thug-life> lulz
So to clarify, thug-life has a life. He lives it the way he wishes, as well as many others on this forum. By calling them nerds is just a stupid way to judge, and you don't even know their back round. We would of never thought someone like thug went to school and other places. So learn facts before you name call!
Thoughts? *This is serious topic, not spam or anything*
